Description: JASP module for identifying candidate Type I errors in
    collections of NHST results. Computes the eJAB01 approximate objective
    Bayes factor for each result, estimates a calibrated threshold C* via
    minimisation of an integrated squared deviation objective, and flags
    results where the p-value rejects the null while eJAB01 supports it.
    Provides calibration, diagnostic QQ, and data summary plots.
